events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Royce O’Neale scored on a tip-in with 0.7 seconds left to complete a triple-double and give the Brooklyn Nets a 109-107 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: O’Neale scores on late tip, Nets top Trail Blazers 109-107

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 28 points and eight assists and the Sacramento Kings beat the San Antonio Spurs 130-112 on Thursday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 28 points, Kings beat Spurs for 5th win a row

headlines.description: — A month into the season, the Los Angeles Clippers are still trying to see the team they're hoping to be.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally to beat Pistons 96-91 in Leonard's return
